# usbliter8 Payload Injector

> **checkra1n/palera1n-style** payload injector + full jailbreak tool for the `usbliter8` SecureROM exploit (A12/A13).

```
                    __    __    __  __       __
     |  |  |  |  | |  \  |  \  |  \ |  |  | |  \
     |  |--|  |  | |  |  |  |  |  | |  |  | |  |
     |  |  |  |__| |__/  |__/  |__/ \__|__/ |__/
  __      __   __   __              __       __
  |  \  / |  \ |  \ |  \  |  |  | |  \    |  \
  |  |  |  |  | |  | |  |  |  |  | |  |    |  |
  |__/   |  |__| |__/ |__/  \__|__| |__/ __|__/
```

Based on the research by **Paradigm Shift** ([usbliter8 PoC](https://github.com/prdgmshift/usbliter8) | [write-up](https://ps.tc/pages/blog-usbliter8.html))

## What is usbliter8?

`usbliter8` is an **unpatchable BootROM exploit** for Apple A12/S4/S5 and A13 SoCs. Like `checkm8`, it exploits a hardware bug in the USB controller and cannot be fixed via software update.

## Project Structure

```
soph1e-ra1n/
├── soph1e_ra1n/          # Host-side tool (Python)
│   ├── gui/app.py               # checkra1n-style desktop GUI
│   ├── cli/main.py              # CLI with 12 commands
│   ├── cli/tui.py               # Interactive terminal UI
│   └── core/                    # Exploit, board, device logic
├── device/                       # Device-side (iOS post-jailbreak)
│   ├── loader/                  # Loader app (SwiftUI Xcode project)
│   ├── bootstrap/               # Bootstrap package (APT sources, scripts)
│   └── scripts/                 # Build & deployment scripts
└── firmware/                    # Pre-built RP2350 UF2 files
```

## GUI (checkra1n-style)

```
soph1e-ra1n gui
```

- **Device pane**: Live status of iDevice + RP2350 board
- **Flash button**: One-click firmware flash to RP2350
- **DFU guide**: Built-in DFU mode instructions
- **Exploit button**: Full exploit workflow with progress bar
- **Post-exploit buttons**: Demote, Boot iBoot, Install Loader
- **Settings panel**: Timeouts, auto-flash, auto-detect, firmware path
- **Console output**: Real-time log window
- **About section**: Device compat info

## CLI (palera1n-style)

```bash
soph1e-ra1n tui          # Interactive terminal UI
soph1e-ra1n gui          # Desktop GUI
soph1e-ra1n exploit      # Run exploit workflow
soph1e-ra1n jailbreak    # Full jailbreak (exploit + bootstrap + loader)
soph1e-ra1n demote       # Demote production mode
soph1e-ra1n boot <file>  # Boot raw iBoot image
soph1e-ra1n status       # Show device status
soph1e-ra1n board        # Show RP2350 board info
soph1e-ra1n flash        # Flash RP2350 firmware
soph1e-ra1n fetch-firmware  # Download latest UF2
soph1e-ra1n build-loader     # Build device-side loader app
soph1e-ra1n build-bootstrap  # Build bootstrap package
```

## Device-Side Loader App

After jailbreaking, a **Loader app** appears on the home screen with:

- **Package manager installer**: One-tap install Sileo, Zebra, or Cydia
- **Bootstrap management**: Reinstall/bootstrap repair
- **System info**: Kernel version, bootchain status, exploit type
- **Tool launchers**: Launch unc0ver, Taurine, etc.

## Complete Jailbreak Workflow

```
Host PC                     RP2350 Board                iPhone/iPad
─────────                   ────────────                ──────────
   │                             │                          │
   ├── Flash firmware ──────────►│                          │
   │                             │                          │
   │◄──── Instructions to DFU ───│                          │
   │                             │◄── Device in DFU ────────┤
   │                             │                          │
   │                             ├── Run exploit ──────────►│
   │                             │  (0.7-1.2s)              │
   │◄──── PWND! Replug to PC ────│                          │
   │                             │                          │
   ├── Demote production ────────│─────────────────────────►│
   ├── Boot custom iBoot ────────│─────────────────────────►│
   ├── Install bootstrap ────────│─────────────────────────►│
   ├── Deploy Loader app ────────│─────────────────────────►│
   │                             │                          │
   │                             │           Loader app on  │
   │                             │           home screen!   │
```

## Hardware Requirements

- **RP2350 board**: Waveshare RP2350 USB-A (recommended), Pico 2, TINY2350
- **Lightning to USB-A cable** (no USB-C)
- **Vulnerable device**: iPhone XR/XS/11 series, iPad Air 3/mini 5/8/9, Apple Watch S4/S5, HomePod mini

## Software Requirements

- Python 3.10+
- `pip install customtkinter pyusb` (for GUI)
- Theos (for building loader app on macOS)

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install
pip install -e .
pip install customtkinter

# Fetch firmware from GitHub
soph1e-ra1n fetch-firmware

# Connect RP2350 (hold BOOTSEL), then:
soph1e-ra1n flash

# Launch GUI
soph1e-ra1n gui
```

